<br>
Where have those days gone?  <br>
<br>
Now you go to the plane of Hate or Dragon Necropolis, or any other high lvl zone and what happens?  It takes 3 hours to even get in the zone, rules are set forth before anybody goes in.  Rules about loot and attacking, and camping, and drops, and god knows what else.  They are plastered on websites like the pages of a Law book from a Judge's private chambers.  Tempers and patients go the oposite way they should, rising and falling.  <br>
<br>
Where did the fun go?  it seems the High the level we reach the less this is a game and some serrious investment.  The higher the Lvl we attain the MORE fun this game should become.<br>
<br>
Now don't missunderstand me.  I know there need to be rules, guidlines to follow.  All games have them, basketball, baseball, poker, chess, horseshoes, you name it.  Rules are set up to keep game play fair and equal and ensure fun for all players.  But now tell me, when you play games with friends, if somebody makes a mistake, how do you react?  A foul in Basketball. Do you kick them out of the game or the group?  If you invite somebody to play poker with you, do they have to wait an hour before they can place any bets or before they can win the pot?  If you have somebody in your game that is cheating, or fouling intentionally what do you do?  yes, then you kick them out and you don't let them play till they can play nice.  So?  you have a problem with somebody then you discipline them.  It just seems a sad day to me when I have to see these kind of rules laid out in plain text for the FAMILY of KoV.  (For a large coalition, like GC, I can moreso see the need for that, because diffrent guilds do things diffrently)<br>
<br>
Guys, this is a game.  People make mistakes.  I was listening to the last time you tried to raid Fear, and seen the other rules for the big raids.  Needing a 'police force' to watch for people who break the rules?  If you break Mez on a mob, and die, you won't get a rez, only a revive and no exp back.  God knows losing exp at 45+ sucks, but it IS only exp.  You don't have a black eye, or a broken limb.  People make a mistake because that's just how we are.  Human, faliable.  And I don't see any forgivness in all this.  If I am grouping with any of KoV, I'll be honest.  I'm not even paying attention to your loot rules.  If something drops that somebody needs, then fine, it's theirs.  If I don't need it, I won't mess with it.  and if I want it for an alt, I'll ask if anybody has a problem with it, and if they do, fine.  It's common courtsy people.  It shouldn't have to be spelled out to the letter of the law for us.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Rules like that just don't build good will.  personally I don't care to be on a raid like that.  (and it's sad that it seems it must be like that)<br>
<br>
Remember the Golden Rule?  then use it! <br>
<br>
I Know I haven't been around much, at least as Atrox.  To be honest, for those of you who didn't know,  Atrox is now and has been retired.  Lvl 54 Cavalier of Marr is no more.  The game was not fun for me, for many of the reasons above and some others as well.  Namely I find that I am disagreeing with the way verant has structured the Paladin class.  The vision in my head of what a Paladin should be is not the same as Verants.  I love that class, and would rather not play them, and pay my respect to those who choose to, than to play something that doesn't fit the immage in my head.  But anyway, I started playing an alt.  He's not guilded, and wonders around, finding grps or grping with a few friends who know of him.  And it is so nice.  We dont' have to write out rules for loot and when you can loot and what you can loot and what you can't loot and who gets to loot what when and if you can't than see sub paragaph w-3.45.  <br>
<br>
And then, THEN I realized what was wrong with Atrox.  It wasn't a game anymore. I had fallen into the trap, and it was serrious. too serrious.  And when I stepped back and played my alt for a few weeks, I finally saw that.  It hit me like a brick.<br>
<br>
As it stands now I play my alt off and on.  I'm not sure if I will keep my account or quit Ever Quest for good.  As it stands now, the only reason I have to stay on EQ are a few very good friends.  My alt has nothing to look forward too but pages of rules and regulations to dictate to him what he can and can't do when and where and how.  As it is now, he will hit the same wall Atrox did.  <br>
<br>
Helping out in Kedge was my honor and a pleasure Kit, and Faewynd.  It is Atrox's last act.  <br>
<br>
I bid thee all a fair well for the time being.  If I decide to keep my alt, now my primary, then perhaps I will see you on some path through Norratth.  May Brell guide your feet, Elorsi give you compassion, Mithanelle grace you with the light of Truth, Tunare grant you sweet passage of time and Karana keep his rains from your head.  It has been a pleasure, and my honor to be there, to help and contriubte to all those who have needed me.  <br>
<br>
Fair thee well. <p>Atrox Runeblade <br>

Warrior-Poet   **  Cavalier of Marr    **   Light from Truth   ** <br>

