May the Truth of Mithaniel guide your blade</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/uatroxruneblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AtroxRuneblade</A> at: 11/8/01 11:05:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/uryland29.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryland29</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Champion</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/9/01 8:47:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub55.ezboard.com/fknightsofvalor76584frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  remember when...</span><hr size=1> I really do wish that we could go without the rules and such for raids...that everyone would abide by the 'Golden Rule'...alas that is just a dream...for somewhere somebody will do something that will piss another person off.  The rules arent meant to be a restriction, but a way to help everyone get along.  Some people may have no problem with loot and such, but others do...it fits into their goals of what they want to get out of this game.  I do agree that the low level vs the high level game play is two completely different worlds.  I do feel that the rules that we have set forth are extremely fair...we are fair with penalties.  In anything rules must exist or their is total anarchy...<br>
<br>
I'm sorry you have lost your desire to play the game Atrox.  I hope you find something that makes you happy with life.  Good luck in whatever you do.<br>
<br>
Ry <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/ubascomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bascomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>KoV member</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/9/01 9:04:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub55.ezboard.com/fknightsofvalor76584frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Remember when...</span><hr size=1> Wow Atrox...<br>
<br>
I must say that you've expressed in words what I've felt for the last 2 months or so.<br>
<br>
I also have noticed that people have told me that I shoulden't be allowed to try for pieces of my epic because I'm only level 41.  I feel if I'm there risking my XP and taking my time I should at least get a roll/a chance to get it.  <br>
<br>
I understand the need for the Loot rules.  I hate to say it, but I'm glad they are there.  It eliminates people argueing during a raid about who gets what and why they deserve to roll or not on it.  That is a good thing, I salute the officers for taking care of this part.<br>
<br>
I think this is all a matter of Greed.  I've been greedy as of late and some of you might know Tamzach and I had a heated discussion about it.  Once she and I were able to connect about the issue, it was clear.  I've had to realize that this IS a game.  I'm going to keep playing with or without that ES Sleeves I really want.  I'm sure that everybody else will as well.  <br>
<br>
I've decided that I'm going to keep throwing Bascomb into the frey during raids.  Keep being agressive.  I figure if I help Tam and the others get their stuff, they'll be there for me.<br>
<br>
I'm not going to give up on my Epic because I'm level 41 and people don't like it.  But I'm not going to push hard to get pieces.  If I'm there and a piece drops and I can roll, you better believe I'm going to do it!<br>
<br>
See you online!<br>
<br>
Amino Et Fide!<br>
<br>
Craig<br>
A.K.A. Bascomb<br>
