May the beauty of Tunare alwasy fill thine eyes <br>
May the Truth of Mithaniel guide your blade</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/ulangleyevocateur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Langley Evocateur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>KoV member</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/10/01 2:55:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub55.ezboard.com/fknightsofvalor76584frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Remember when...</span><hr size=1> The rules or guidelines are insurance against arguements.  Call them what you will.  Why does KoV need them when previously they did not?  Perhaps with the growing number of higher level members and the multigroup raids that become the norm is the reason.  Why would we need complicated looting policies if there are five of us at orc1 in EC?  Rules are like all laws, they really only keep the honest honest, there are many that will not heed them anyways.  The work put into forging a workable looting policy is what should be the focus and thanks to those who have spent hours and hours of their time trying to find a way to keep us all happy.  These rules are not meant to be an insult to people, but a way to make the raid organizer have something to base a decision on.  How would you propose 36 people standing over something of value decide on the spur of the moment who should have?  Their would be no need to loot anything because it would all decay before we could decide who gets it ).  The rules need to be in place for all to digest and now we are doing just that.  I am very happy with them and see a need for them.<br>
<br>
Lang  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub55.ezboard.com/bknightsofvalor76584.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jook>Jook</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>KoV member</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/11/01 5:27:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub55.ezboard.com/fknightsofvalor76584frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=115.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Remember when...</span><hr size=1> The rules went up becuse the game is different at level 52 than it is at 25.<br>
